label lbl_our_first_shift:
#[Office, outside the manager's office, afternoon - “Our first shift”  - main_story =96]

#-scene starts with the Mc and Mr Fistem finalizing their conversation outside of his office as Mr Fistem is about to instruct [povname] on what his duties are-

    scene bg officefloor_day
    with fade
    show pov bored at left
    with dissolve
    show mrf bored_talk at right
    with dissolve
    mrf "-and that correlates to the legal disclaimer number 728 that strictly specifies that “TRC” is not and will not be responsible for any injury caused to employees during the unlikely and borderline impossible event of a robot uprising."
    show pov embarrassed at left
    mrf "Alright, that covers the very basics of the light employee introduction rule of conduct and the signing of your NDA’s and liability waivers."
    show pov embarrassed_talk at left
    show mrf smirk at right
    pov "I’m not comfortable with the fact that something the company says is borderline impossible to happen still needs me to sign a paper for it."
    show pov embarrassed at left
    show mrf smirk_talk at right
    mrf "Hey, that’s the kind of stuff you have to deal with when you work in the frontlines of the technological era."
    mrf "We are making the future here, kid! People gotta future proof themselves in case we are unknowingly headed for disaster."
    show pov confused at left
    show mrf neutral_talk at right
    mrf "What today is a paranoid exaggeration, tomorrow could be called incredible foresight."
    show pov confused at left
    show mrf smirk at right
    pov "I guess I can see some sense in that, doesn’t make me feel any better."
    show pov confused at left
    show mrf neutral_talk at right
    mrf "Think about it this way, kid."
    mrf "You know how in school they teach ya not to stick your little dinger in a girl without a “party hat” on?"
    show pov embarrassed at left
    show mrf smirk_talk at right
    mrf "Well, in the corporate world, you don’t get to work in any place without making sure the company has as little responsibility over your well being as possible."
    show pov embarrassed_talk at left
    show mrf smirk at right
    pov "I could have understood it without the condom metaphor but alright."
    show pov smirk at left
    show mrf smirk_talk at right
    mrf "Just be thankful that if such a thing were to happen, we are as far away from any mechanical doohickey that could turn hostile."
    show pov embarrassed at left
    show mrf bored_talk at right
    mrf "Well, except maybe the copy machine."
    mrf "I swear that stupid thing is sentient and has it out for me."
    show mrf shocked_talk at right
    mrf "Luckily now we have you to deal with it."
    show pov bored_talk at left
    show mrf shocked_talk at right
    pov "Lucky me."
    show pov bored at left
    show mrf bored_talk at right
    mrf "Alright. Legal runaround is over and we can focus on what you are going to be doing here."
    show pov smirk_talk at left
    show mrf smirk at right
    pov "I’m going to guess it involves the copy machine?"
    show pov smirk at left
    show mrf smirk_talk at right
    mrf "You are perceptive then."
    show pov embarrassed at left
    show mrf bored_talk at right
    mrf "Yes, while the guys here focus on their tech support work, I’m going to need you to deal with the stuff around the office that can normally take time that they could be using by memorizing our systems and solving technical issues on the phone."
    mrf "You know, the kind of stuff that messes with the workflow and puts them in a bad mood."
    show pov confused at left
    show mrf neutral_talk at right
    mrf "Primarily speaking, I want you to deal with the copy machine whenever it jams, sort out some paperwork we need to periodically send to different departments and take these guys coffee orders and get it for us."
    show pov confused_talk at left
    show mrf neutral at right
    pov "Sounds simple enough, do you really need an intern for all of that?"
    show pov confused at left
    show mrf smirk_talk at right
    mrf "Don’t ever underestimate small problems, kid."
    show pov shocked at left
    show mrf confused_talk at right
    mrf "It’s no secret that this department was a last minute idea so we have to make due with the scraps until our earnings report satisfies the higher ups and lets us upgrade what we have."
    show mrf smirk_talk at right
    mrf "A lot of things in this department so far have been hand me downs from other departments and the depths of the supply closet so they don’t work up to standards."
    show pov embarrassed at left
    show mrf bored_talk at right
    mrf "The copying machine is probably from around the time you were born and it tends to jam a lot."
    mrf "The old coffee maker we had was a relic and disgusting, not to mention it’s now broken because I burned my hand so I punched it."
    show mrf confused_talk at right
    mrf "And because of how the company is integrating this new department into the workflow, we have a lot of emails we need to reply to regarding our metrics and performance."
    show pov confused at left
    show mrf shocked_talk at right
    mrf "All of these things pile up and create a huge distraction for everybody -"
    mrf "- which in turn affects morale and productivity, which will make our metrics as a department bad-"
    mrf "-which will lead to the higher ups refusing our requests to upgrade our equipment and it all forms a vicious cycle that will end up with this department through the floor and us fired or demoted for incompetence."
    show pov bored_talk at left
    show mrf confused at right
    pov "Alright, I see the problem now."
    show pov smirk_talk at left
    pov "Still, shouldn’t the higher ups be a little more understanding here? I mean, you guys are working with scraps."
    show pov shocked at left
    show mrf smirk_talk at right
    mrf "Kid, I’m about to teach you a very important lesson about the corporate world and life in general."
    show mrf neutral_talk at right
    mrf "Whatever you may consider to be a real problem in your workspace or life, may be considered as nothing more than an excuse for you to be lazy for someone sitting in a better chair than you."
    show pov sad at left
    show mrf smirk_talk at right
    mrf "Higher ups don’t care about what problems you may have unless it affects their wallets directly."
    show mrf bored_talk at right
    mrf "Especially if you are so below them that they forget you exist."
    show pov embarrassed at left
    show mrf neutral_talk at right
    mrf "For them, we aren’t people, we are gears in the machine that prints them money."
    mrf "And when those gears aren’t working as well as they want it, they get thrown out and replaced without a second thought."
    show pov embarrassed_talk at left
    show mrf neutral at right
    pov "Well, that’s a dark way to look at it."
    show pov embarrassed at left
    show mrf smirk_talk at right
    mrf "That’s the reality of the corporate world, kiddo. Get used to it if you wanna go far in the industry."
    show pov smirk_talk at left
    show mrf smirk at right
    pov "Not sure if I want to, to be honest."
    show pov embarrassed at left
    show mrf smirk_talk at right
    mrf "Then you are a lot smarter than what I gave you credit for, kid."
    mrf "But, since you are here, then you are gonna need to pull your own weight."
    show mrf neutral_talk at right
    mrf "Intern or not, you are part of our team, so your metrics are our metrics as well."
    show pov neutral at left
    show mrf confused_talk at right
    mrf "Your job is to keep all these distractions away from the rest of the team as much as you can."
    show pov confused at left
    show mrf shocked_talk at right
    mrf "If you can, then these fools can concentrate on their job and we may be able to get this department somewhere."
    show mrf bored_talk at right
    mrf "Yes, it may be busy work and yes, perhaps it wasn’t what you wanted out of a job here."
    mrf "But it’s still important work that piles up quickly, so I’m counting on you to keep it under control."
    show pov shocked at left
    show mrf confused_talk at right
    mrf "You do good by us and I’ll make sure you are rewarded for it."
    show pov confused_talk at left
    show mrf confused at right
    pov "I thought this was an unpaid internship?"
    show pov confused at left
    show mrf bored_talk at right
    mrf "Maybe so, but I take care of my people and as long as you work with the team, I’ll make sure you get your share."
    show pov embarrassed at left
    show mrf smirk_talk at right
    mrf "Do we have a deal?"
    show pov embarrassed_talk at left
    show mrf smirk at right
    pov "Sounds good to me, I’ll give you my best."
    show pov embarrassed at left
    show mrf neutral_talk at right
    mrf "That’s what I like to hear!"
    show pov neutral at left
    mrf "Alright, let’s give all these duties of yours a test run so that you can get started."
    show pov confused at left
    show mrf smirk_talk at right
    mrf "What do you want to try out first?"
    $ main_story = 97
    jump lbl_office_jobs_tutorials

